Miroslav Čepický adds: "We are open to negotiations with potential virtual operators, and this in terms of the distribution of expenditure and infrastructure.
We consider this to be the biggest input from the customers' point of view.
Vodafone's main strategy in this field is in the partner with whom to establish a shared network for a fast mobile internet."
Responsible offices - with uña operators and meat
The progress of mobile operators can easily be understood, but the entry of another operator would mean increasing competition which would lead to a price drop and thereby a decrease in profits.
